text_1: In another successful anti-piracy operation , Navy warship on Saturday repulsed an attack on a merchant vessel in the Gulf of Aden and nabbed 23 Somali and Yemeni sea brigands , in a show of resolve to weed out the menace that affected maritime trade in the region .

text_2: New Delhi / Mumbai : An Indian warship foiled a five - boat pirate attack on merchant vessels transiting the Gulf of Aden on Friday capturing 26 Somani brigands on three of the skiffs and confiscating their weapons .

text_1: New Delhi / Mumbai : An Indian warship foiled a five - boat pirate attack on merchant vessels transiting the Gulf of Aden on Friday capturing 26 Somani brigands on three of the skiffs and confiscating their weapons .
prev_text_1: Published on : Fri , 11 Nov 2011 at 09 : 56 IST
text_2: A five - boat pirate attack on merchant vessels transiting the Gulf of Aden was foiled by an Indian warship that was on escort duty , capturing 26 Somani brigands on three of the skiffs and confiscating their weapons , a naval officer said here Friday .

text_1: Raj K . Chohan was walking alongside parked cars on 117th Street and 97th Avenue at about 7 p . m . when she was struck by a gray 2013 Toyota Camry , which then sped off , according to cops .
prev_text_1: A 59 - year - old woman was killed in a hit - and - run crash while visiting a former neighbor to welcome his new daughter - in - law to the family Friday evening , and the man allegedly behind the wheel of the car that hit her was charged with driving drunk , police and the woman ’ s friend said .
text_2: An initial investigation of the scene revealed that Chohan had been walking alongside the parked cars on 117th Street when she was struck by a vehicle heading northbound , police said .
prev_text_2: EMS crews rushed Chohan to Jamaica Hospital for treatment , where she was later pronounced dead .

tokens_1: Raj K . Chohan was walking alongside parked cars on 117th Street and 97th Avenue at about 7 p . m . when she was struck by a gray 2013 Toyota Camry , which then sped off , according to cops .
tokens_2: An initial investigation of the scene revealed that Chohan had been walking alongside the parked cars on 117th Street when she was struck by a vehicle heading northbound , police said .

tokens_1: Billy King spun the 76ers' head coach revolving door again yesterday , pushing out Jim O'Brien after just one season and bringing in Maurice Cheeks , the popular former Sixers player and assistant coach , as O'Brien's replacement .

tokens_1: Authorities have released the name of a 66-year-old woman who was walking outside the Sam 's Club in Bloomington when she was struck and killed by a motorist .
tokens_2: According to police , Anthony LaSalle , 36 , of Minneapolis , hit and killed a 66-year-old LuAnn Marie Johnson in the parking lot of the Bloomington Sam 's Club Wednesday night .

text_1: An accounting firm employee who was fired last week shot and killed a woman and wounded two men Monday at the suburban Detroit building where he worked , then led officers on a high - speed chase , police said .
prev_text_1: Suspect had been fired last week by Troy , Mich . , company
text_2: A fired accountant bought a shotgun the day after he lost his job , then returned to the office the following week and opened fire on his bosses , wounding both and killing a receptionist , the Associated Press reported .

tokens_1: An accounting firm employee who was fired last week shot and killed a woman and wounded two men Monday at the suburban Detroit building where he worked , then led officers on a high - speed chase , police said .
tokens_2: A fired accountant bought a shotgun the day after he lost his job , then returned to the office the following week and opened fire on his bosses , wounding both and killing a receptionist , the Associated Press reported .

text_1: Even as Oscar organizers on Friday unveiled Hugh Jackman as the host of their gala film awards , the prospect of a U.S. actors strike was casting a long shadow over whether Hollywood 's big show would go on as usual .
text_2: Hugh Jackman , the Australian actor known to film audiences for playing a furry comic-book hero in the X-Men movies , will be host of the 81st incarnation of the Oscars , the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences announced on Friday .
prev_text_2: The producers of the Academy Awards are counting on a mutant wolverine who is People magazine 's reigning Sexiest Man Alive to inject some desperately needed razzle-dazzle into their annual telecast .

text_2: But the 76ers , while underachieving at 9-14 when Cheeks was fired Saturday morning , were not an embarassment when they went on the court , not a disjointed bunch that clearly was no longer listening to or playing for its coach .

tokens_1: Indian Navy patrolling the Gulf of Aden yesterday thwarted a multi - boat attack by sea brigands on merchant vessels , apprehending 26 Somali pirates and confiscating arms and ammunition , in the fifth successful anti - piracy operation since September .
tokens_2: A five - boat pirate attack on merchant vessels transiting the Gulf of Aden was foiled by an Indian warship that was on escort duty , capturing 26 Somani brigands on three of the skiffs and confiscating their weapons , a naval officer said here Friday .

text_1: Maurice Cheeks was fired Saturday as coach of the Philadelphia 76ers , who are slumping at 9-14 a year after making the playoffs .

tokens_1: The BBC reports 56-year - old Allan Matthews pleaded guilty Wednesday to removing another man 's left testicle at an Australian motel despite not being qualified to practice medicine .
tokens_2: AAP A DIY " doctor " accused of slicing off a man 's testicle in a NSW motel room has pleaded guilty to a charge of illicitly removing another person 's bodily tissue .

text_1: The Daily Beast reported Thursday that a source said to be an ally of AG Jeff Sessions detailed a new effort on the emails front that includes finding more out about the classified correspondence allegedly sent via Clinton's server, as well as who knew about the info there.
prev_text_1: Meanwhile, officials note the DOJ is also re-examining whether there was more to the Clinton email server that hadn't been thoroughly wrapped up before that case was closed.
text_2: Officials' questions include how much classified information was sent over Clinton's server; who put that information into an unclassified environment, and how; and which investigators knew about these matters and when.

tokens_1: So he searched the basement , and " found myself in what I am pretty certain is the 1750s historic tavern , " he says .
tokens_2: He decided to poke around and , in the basement , Woodward found what he believes are Colonial - era , hand - hewn and hand - planed joists and foundation walls .

text_1: From the complaint: "The macho bullying atmosphere at Magic Leap fosters a dysfunctional culture which creates chaos and lack of process and structure, hinders the company from achieving key product deadlines (including launch, which has shifted back at least 4 times in Campbell's 1.5 years at the company) and, literally, prevented Campbell from doing the job she was hired to do or achieving the goals she and Abovitz had discussed during her initial interview: helping with the "pink/blue problem" or making Magic Leap less of a "boys club.""
prev_text_1: Campbell, who is suing for Magic Leap for sex discrimination, retaliation and hostile work environment, connects the lack of women in Magic Leap's leadership and engineering department with claims of missed internal deadlines.
text_2: Ultimately, these workplace problems, the lawsuit reads, "renders it so dysfunctional it continues to delay the launch of a product that attracted billions of investment dollars."
prev_text_2: The company is accused of violating the Title VII of the Civil Rights Act of 1964, which prohibits employers from discriminating against employees on the basis of sex, race, color, national origin and religion.

tokens_1: From the complaint : " The macho bullying atmosphere at Magic Leap fosters a dysfunctional culture which creates chaos and lack of process and structure , hinders the company from achieving key product deadlines ( including launch , which has shifted back at least 4 times in Campbell 's 1.5 years at the company ) and , literally , prevented Campbell from doing the job she was hired to do or achieving the goals she and Abovitz had discussed during her initial interview : helping with the " pink / blue problem " or making Magic Leap less of a " boys club . " "
tokens_2: Ultimately , these workplace problems , the lawsuit reads , " renders it so dysfunctional it continues to delay the launch of a product that attracted billions of investment dollars . "

text_1: As the Blaze notes, Republicans want to scale back the Supplemental Nutritional Assistance Program-arguing that the end of the recession should indicate less need-and trimmed $8.6 billion and 850,000 people from its rolls with last year's farm bill.
prev_text_1: The jump signals what Reuters says is a "lop-sided" economic recovery that has left low-income people behind, but it also underscores a fundamental partisan divide over social welfare programs.
text_2: The GOP has said the end of the recession should allow Congress to reduce spending on food stamps.
prev_text_2: The debate over food stamps has led to a sort of chicken-and-egg argument between Republicans and Democrats.

text_1: Magic Leap CEO Rony Abovitz Getty A newly filed lawsuit by a former Magic Leap VP alleges that the company is a hostile working place for women, a condition that has led to the company missing internal deadlines, according to the complaint.
text_2: The lawsuit alleged Campbell was fired because the company's CEO, Rony Abovitz, refused to acknowledge the misogyny within the company and address a hostile work environment.
prev_text_2: Tannen Campbell, Magic Leap's former vice president of strategic marketing and brand identity, filed the suit in a federal court in the Southern District of Florida.

text_1: As the Blaze notes, Republicans want to scale back the Supplemental Nutritional Assistance Program-arguing that the end of the recession should indicate less need-and trimmed $8.6 billion and 850,000 people from its rolls with last year's farm bill.
prev_text_1: The jump signals what Reuters says is a "lop-sided" economic recovery that has left low-income people behind, but it also underscores a fundamental partisan divide over social welfare programs.
text_2: Republicans have tried since 2013 to cut food stamp spending, as part of their overall plan to slow spending and get control of the budget deficit.
prev_text_2: The number finally dipped from that peak in 2014, but just a little, to about 46 million people.

tokens_1: An augmented reality startup is being sued for sex discrimination by the very female executive it hired to make it less of a " boy 's club , " the Guardian reports .
tokens_2: Augmented reality startup Magic Leap is being sued for sexual discrimination by an executive who was hired to help it appeal to women .

text_1: From the complaint: "The macho bullying atmosphere at Magic Leap fosters a dysfunctional culture which creates chaos and lack of process and structure, hinders the company from achieving key product deadlines (including launch, which has shifted back at least 4 times in Campbell's 1.5 years at the company) and, literally, prevented Campbell from doing the job she was hired to do or achieving the goals she and Abovitz had discussed during her initial interview: helping with the "pink/blue problem" or making Magic Leap less of a "boys club.""
prev_text_1: Campbell, who is suing for Magic Leap for sex discrimination, retaliation and hostile work environment, connects the lack of women in Magic Leap's leadership and engineering department with claims of missed internal deadlines.
text_2: Missed deadlines Campbell, who is suing for Magic Leap for sex discrimination, retaliation and hostile work environment, connects the lack of women in Magic Leap's leadership and engineering department with claims of missed internal deadlines.
prev_text_2: Magic Leap did not immediately return requests for comment.

tokens_1: From the complaint : " The macho bullying atmosphere at Magic Leap fosters a dysfunctional culture which creates chaos and lack of process and structure , hinders the company from achieving key product deadlines ( including launch , which has shifted back at least 4 times in Campbell 's 1.5 years at the company ) and , literally , prevented Campbell from doing the job she was hired to do or achieving the goals she and Abovitz had discussed during her initial interview : helping with the " pink / blue problem " or making Magic Leap less of a " boys club . " "
tokens_2: Missed deadlines Campbell , who is suing for Magic Leap for sex discrimination , retaliation and hostile work environment , connects the lack of women in Magic Leap 's leadership and engineering department with claims of missed internal deadlines .

text_1: In 2014, an estimated 16 million children, or about one in five, received food stamp assistance compared with the roughly 9 million children, or one in eight, that received this form of assistance prior to the recession.
prev_text_1: The rate of children living with married parents who receive food stamps has doubled since 2007.
text_2: WASHINGTON The number of children in the United States relying on food stamps for a meal spiked to 16 million last year, according federal data, signaling a lopsided economic recovery in which lower income families are still lagging behind.

tokens_1: Founded in 2010 , the company is developing an augmented reality headset that superimposes virtual objects onto the real world , and has amassed $ 1.4 billion from the likes Google and Alibaba , despite no announced product for sale yet .
tokens_2: The company , a startup best known for securing a valuation in the billions despite never publicly demonstrating its technology , is being sued by Tannen Campbell , its former head of , and later vice - president of , strategic marketing and brand identity .

text_1: Magic Leap CEO Rony Abovitz Getty A newly filed lawsuit by a former Magic Leap VP alleges that the company is a hostile working place for women, a condition that has led to the company missing internal deadlines, according to the complaint.
text_2: Missed deadlines Campbell, who is suing for Magic Leap for sex discrimination, retaliation and hostile work environment, connects the lack of women in Magic Leap's leadership and engineering department with claims of missed internal deadlines.
prev_text_2: Magic Leap did not immediately return requests for comment.

text_1: Meanwhile, some other highlights from the Census numbers: 27% of children live in single-parent homes, three times the 9% who did in 1960 10% of kids live with a grandparent, 15% have a stay-at-home mom, 0.6% have a stay-at-home dad, and 38% have at least one foreign-born parent 48% of households are made up of married couples, down from 76% in 1940 Americans are continuing to marry later, at a median age of 29 for men and 27 for women; that's up from 24 and 21 in 1947
prev_text_1: Democrats, meanwhile, argue that it's too soon to scale back the program.
text_2: Of the 73.7 million children under 18 in the United States, 27 percent were living in single parent homes last year, tripling the 9 percent in 1960.
prev_text_2: Other findings of the survey show a rapidly changing America in which more children are being raised in single-parent homes and more young people are delaying marriage.

tokens_1: Meanwhile , some other highlights from the Census numbers : 27 % of children live in single - parent homes , three times the 9 % who did in 1960 10 % of kids live with a grandparent , 15 % have a stay - at - home mom , 0.6 % have a stay - at - home dad , and 38 % have at least one foreign - born parent 48 % of households are made up of married couples , down from 76 % in 1940 Americans are continuing to marry later , at a median age of 29 for men and 27 for women ; that 's up from 24 and 21 in 1947
tokens_2: Of the 73.7 million children under 18 in the United States , 27 percent were living in single parent homes last year , tripling the 9 percent in 1960 .

text_1: There are roughly 73.7 million kids running around America, and about 16 million, or nearly one in five, of them are doing so fueled by food stamps, according to US Census data out yesterday.
text_2: The roughly one in five children who received food stamps in 2014 surpassed pre-recession levels, when one in eight or 9 million children were on food stamps, according to the U.S. Census survey of American families released on Wednesday Republicans in Congress have sought to cut back on the Supplemental Nutritional Assistance Program or food stamp program as part of a larger plan to balance the budget.
prev_text_2: WASHINGTON The number of children in the United States relying on food stamps for a meal spiked to 16 million last year, according federal data, signaling a lopsided economic recovery in which lower income families are still lagging behind.

tokens_1: There are roughly 73.7 million kids running around America , and about 16 million , or nearly one in five , of them are doing so fueled by food stamps , according to US Census data out yesterday .
tokens_2: The roughly one in five children who received food stamps in 2014 surpassed pre - recession levels , when one in eight or 9 million children were on food stamps , according to the U.S. Census survey of American families released on Wednesday Republicans in Congress have sought to cut back on the Supplemental Nutritional Assistance Program or food stamp program as part of a larger plan to balance the budget .

text_1: Meanwhile, some other highlights from the Census numbers: 27% of children live in single-parent homes, three times the 9% who did in 1960 10% of kids live with a grandparent, 15% have a stay-at-home mom, 0.6% have a stay-at-home dad, and 38% have at least one foreign-born parent 48% of households are made up of married couples, down from 76% in 1940 Americans are continuing to marry later, at a median age of 29 for men and 27 for women; that's up from 24 and 21 in 1947
prev_text_1: Democrats, meanwhile, argue that it's too soon to scale back the program.
text_2: Other findings of the survey show a rapidly changing America in which more children are being raised in single-parent homes and more young people are delaying marriage.
prev_text_2: The final farm bill signed into law trimmed $8.6 billion from the program, eliminating benefits for about 850,000 people, according to estimates by anti-hunger advocates.

tokens_1: Meanwhile , some other highlights from the Census numbers : 27 % of children live in single - parent homes , three times the 9 % who did in 1960 10 % of kids live with a grandparent , 15 % have a stay - at - home mom , 0.6 % have a stay - at - home dad , and 38 % have at least one foreign - born parent 48 % of households are made up of married couples , down from 76 % in 1940 Americans are continuing to marry later , at a median age of 29 for men and 27 for women ; that 's up from 24 and 21 in 1947
tokens_2: Other findings of the survey show a rapidly changing America in which more children are being raised in single - parent homes and more young people are delaying marriage .

text_1: Police said the 52-year-old victim posted an online ad "requesting assistance with a medical issue".
prev_text_1: Allan George Matthews, 56, admitted to "removing tissue" from the man "without consent or authority" at a motel in Port Macquarie, north of Sydney.
text_2: The 52-year-old alleged victim attended the motel room after posting an advertisement online requesting assistance with a medical issue, police claim.
prev_text_2: It is the crown's case that Matthews is not qualified or authorised to perform such a procedure, and is not a qualified or registered medical practitioner.

tokens_1: "Maternal instinct" and a "solutions-oriented" personality are what a 46-year-old Pennsylvania mom says helped her survive a treacherous trek over more than 25 miles of the Grand Canyon to find help for her stranded family, after their car got stuck in a blizzard, Karen Klein tells NBC News.
tokens_2: NEWLINE_CHAR After walking nearly 26 miles , she eventually sought refuge in an empty cabin near the Grand Canyon 's north rim .

text_1: A former aide says Rep. Trent Franks offered her $5 million to act as a surrogate for he and his wife, the AP reports.
text_2: A former staffer also alleged that Franks tried to persuade a female aide that they were in love by having her read an article that described how a person knows they're in love with someone, the sources said.
prev_text_2: He became the third lawmaker this week alone to announce that he will step down after being accused of sexual misconduct.

tokens_2: He became the third lawmaker this week alone to announce that he will step down after being accused of sexual misconduct .

text_1: Around 5,000 demonstrators flooded into the streets of a city considered safe enough to be in the vanguard of a crucial security transition, after Friday prayers ended, and many headed straight for the U.N. mission.
prev_text_1: The Taliban said they had no role in the Kandahar violence or Friday's assault on the U.N. office in the usually peaceful city of Mazar-i-Sharif, after both provincial governors and a senior U.N. official suggested an insurgent role.
text_2: Thousands of people took to the streets in Kandahar city on Saturday, a day after a deadly attack on UN staff.
prev_text_2: Eight people have been killed in Afghanistan as protests continue against the burning of the Quran by a controversial US pastor.

tokens_1: When the Kleins ' car got stuck in a ditch during a snowstorm and they could n't get cellphone service , they decided Karen , a triathlete , should head out for help .
tokens_2: Karen Klein 's love for her family fueled her fight for survival , driving her through a 26-mile hike through a blizzard to get help after her vehicle got stuck in a forest ditch in the Grand Canyon this weekend .

text_1: The lawsuit, which also alleges a hostile work environment and retaliation, claims the sexist culture at Magic Leap created a "dysfunctional" workplace and is part of the reason the company has yet to actually release a product despite being valued at billions of dollars.
prev_text_1: Campbell says she and other female employees were ignored when giving input on the design of the product and its marketing.
text_2: The company, a startup best known for securing a valuation in the billions despite never publicly demonstrating its technology, is being sued by Tannen Campbell, its former head of, and later vice-president of, strategic marketing and brand identity.
prev_text_2: Augmented reality startup Magic Leap is being sued for sexual discrimination by an executive who was hired to help it appeal to women.

text_1: In addition to performing surgery without being a doctor, Matthews also pleaded guilty to gun and drug charges.
prev_text_1: Authorities say a raid of Matthews' home last month turned up medical equipment, seven guns, and four bottles of what may be amyl nitrate.
text_2: He also pleaded guilty in court this week to illegally possessing a gun and two counts of possessing or attempting to prescribe a restricted substance.
prev_text_2: Prosecutors alleged that Matthews was not authorised to perform such a procedure as he was not a qualified or registered medical practitioner.

text_1: Now a preservationist thinks he's found the historic site-and if he's right, it could be the oldest building in Manhattan.
prev_text_1: In 1783, after the British soldiers left New York City, George Washington is believed to have stopped for a celebratory drink at the Bull's Head tavern.
text_2: If it is indeed the home of the legendary watering hole, the discovery could mean that the building that is perhaps Manhattan's oldest is slated to demolished.
prev_text_2: NEW YORK (CBSNewYork) - A preservationist says he has found evidence that a Manhattan building is the former site of an 18th-century tavern where George Washington is believed to have enjoyed a celebratory drink during the American Revolution.

text_1: When Tannen Campbell was hired by Magic Leap in 2015, the Florida company had no women in leadership roles and its only idea to make its product female-friendly was to release a pink version, according to Forbes.
prev_text_1: An augmented reality startup is being sued for sex discrimination by the very female executive it hired to make it less of a "boy's club," the Guardian reports.
text_2: Advertisement "Sadly, because Magic Leap seldom hires and does not actively recruit female candidates, the company loses competitive advantage to products like Microsoft's Hololens.
prev_text_2: "The macho bullying atmosphere at Magic Leap fosters a dysfunctional culture which creates chaos and lack of process and structure, hinders the company from achieving key product deadlines (including launch, which has shifted back at least 4 times in Campbell's 1.5 years at the company) and, literally, prevented Campbell from doing the job she was hired to do or achieving the goals she and Abovitz had discussed during her initial interview: helping with the "pink/blue problem" or making Magic Leap less of a "boys club.""

text_1: Missed deadlines Campbell, who is suing for Magic Leap for sex discrimination, retaliation and hostile work environment, connects the lack of women in Magic Leap's leadership and engineering department with claims of missed internal deadlines.
prev_text_1: Magic Leap did not immediately return requests for comment.
text_2: Ultimately, these workplace problems, the lawsuit reads, "renders it so dysfunctional it continues to delay the launch of a product that attracted billions of investment dollars."
prev_text_2: The company is accused of violating the Title VII of the Civil Rights Act of 1964, which prohibits employers from discriminating against employees on the basis of sex, race, color, national origin and religion.

text_1: Republicans have tried since 2013 to cut food stamp spending, as part of their overall plan to slow spending and get control of the budget deficit.
prev_text_1: The number finally dipped from that peak in 2014, but just a little, to about 46 million people.
text_2: The roughly one in five children who received food stamps in 2014 surpassed pre-recession levels, when one in eight or 9 million children were on food stamps, according to the U.S. Census survey of American families released on Wednesday Republicans in Congress have sought to cut back on the Supplemental Nutritional Assistance Program or food stamp program as part of a larger plan to balance the budget.
prev_text_2: WASHINGTON The number of children in the United States relying on food stamps for a meal spiked to 16 million last year, according federal data, signaling a lopsided economic recovery in which lower income families are still lagging behind.

tokens_1: Republicans have tried since 2013 to cut food stamp spending , as part of their overall plan to slow spending and get control of the budget deficit .
tokens_2: The roughly one in five children who received food stamps in 2014 surpassed pre - recession levels , when one in eight or 9 million children were on food stamps , according to the U.S. Census survey of American families released on Wednesday Republicans in Congress have sought to cut back on the Supplemental Nutritional Assistance Program or food stamp program as part of a larger plan to balance the budget .

text_1: The U.S. Census Bureau reported Wednesday that 16 million children living in America received food stamps in 2014, or about one out of every five kids.
text_2: WASHINGTON The number of children in the United States relying on food stamps for a meal spiked to 16 million last year, according federal data, signaling a lopsided economic recovery in which lower income families are still lagging behind.

prev_text_1: The rate of children living with married parents who receive food stamps has doubled since 2007.
text_2: The roughly one in five children who received food stamps in 2014 surpassed pre-recession levels, when one in eight or 9 million children were on food stamps, according to the U.S. Census survey of American families released on Wednesday Republicans in Congress have sought to cut back on the Supplemental Nutritional Assistance Program or food stamp program as part of a larger plan to balance the budget.

text_1: The number of children receiving food stamps remains higher than it was before the start of the Great Recession in 2007, according to the U.S. Census Bureau's annual Families and Living Arrangements table package released today.

tokens_1: The number of children receiving food stamps remains higher than it was before the start of the Great Recession in 2007 , according to the U.S. Census Bureau 's annual Families and Living Arrangements table package released today .
tokens_2: The roughly one in five children who received food stamps in 2014 surpassed pre - recession levels , when one in eight or 9 million children were on food stamps , according to the U.S. Census survey of American families released on Wednesday Republicans in Congress have sought to cut back on the Supplemental Nutritional Assistance Program or food stamp program as part of a larger plan to balance the budget .

tokens_1: On Monday , a new lawsuit alleged that the Plantation , Fla.-based company promoted a sexist work environment and used misleading marketing materials that inaccurately depicted the product 's capabilities .
tokens_2: The lawsuit alleged Campbell was fired because the company 's CEO , Rony Abovitz , refused to acknowledge the misogyny within the company and address a hostile work environment .

text_1: Campbell says she and other female employees were ignored when giving input on the design of the product and its marketing.
prev_text_1: The lawsuit states Campbell was asked to put together a presentation on the lack of gender diversity at the company, but it took seven months for Magic Leap's chief executive to show up for the presentation, and he left in the middle of it.
text_2: The warnings were "ignored in favor of her male colleagues' assertions that the images and videos presented on Magic Leap's website and on YouTube were 'aspirational,' and not Magic Leap's version of 'alternate facts,' " the lawsuit said in an apparent reference to U.S. President Donald J. Trump counselor Kellyanne Conway's infamous use of the term "alternative facts."
prev_text_2: In the lawsuit, Campbell said she brought up concerns that the company was showing off marketing material that didn't accurately reflect what Magic Leap's technology could actually do.

text_1: There are roughly 73.7 million kids running around America, and about 16 million, or nearly one in five, of them are doing so fueled by food stamps, according to US Census data out yesterday.
text_2: The U.S. Census Bureau reported Wednesday that 16 million children living in America received food stamps in 2014, or about one out of every five kids.

text_1: Although a U.N. team verified the withdrawal of all Syrian troops from Lebanon on April 26, the US and Lebanese opposition leaders insisted that Syrian intelligence agents remained in Lebanon.

text_1: Kempthorne added his department is not taking a position on why the ice is melting; that's beyond the scope of the Endangered Species Act.
prev_text_1: On December 27, 2006, U.S. Interior Secretary, Dirk Kempthorne, announced a proposal to list the polar bear as a threatened species because of sea ice loss.
text_2: The administration has prohibited its scientists, when acting as government representatives, from linking human factors to polar bears and global warming.
prev_text_2: The designation prohibits federal agencies from authorizing anything, including oil drilling, that would harm the bears' habitat.

text_1: Several law suits, including a class action suit have been filed by pet owners whose pets died.
prev_text_1: The FDA is investigating the recall and the Canadian factory where the pet was produced is temporarily shut down.
text_2: The recall has led to at least three lawsuits against Menu Foods from owners seeking compensation for the loss of beloved family pets, high veterinary bills and continuing care costs for surviving animals.
prev_text_2: Ten confirmed cases of diet-related renal failure were diagnosed at a Manhattan veterinary medical center where one cat died.

text_1: Juan Manuel Alvarez, 29 year old, was found guilty and sentenced to life in prison without parole by a Los Angeles jury, for murder of 11 people and injuring 180 others.
text_2: The jury convicted Alvarez on all charges and recommended life without parole instead of death.
prev_text_2: LA County DDAs Cathryn Brougham and John Monaghan said he was trying to get attention from his estranged wife.

text_1: On March 1st, Major General Weightman, Chief of Walter Reed, was fired by Army Secretary Harvey because the army had lost trust and confidence in him.
text_2: Army Secretary Francis Harvey, who dismissed Walter Reed commander General George Weightman the previous Thursday, has resigned himself.
prev_text_2: A Defense Department spokesman said that the Disability Evaluation System will be improved.

text_1: In June, 2007, toy maker RC2 Corp. recalled 1.5 million Thomas & Friends toys that were decorated with lead paint, which can cause long-term neurological damage.
text_2: Recently, RC2 Corp. recalled 1.5 million wooden Thomas & Friends trains and accessories, and Mattel recalled nearly 1 million of its Fisher-Price toy characters, all Chinese-manufactured toys found to contain excessive amounts of lead in their paint.
prev_text_2: Recalled toys include a toy found to be filled with kerosene, an infant rattle that was a choking hazard and toy drums sets and bears recalled for lead paint.

text_1: The rapid breakdown of the floating ice shelves observed in recent years, the experts said, could destabilize land-based ice sheets and glaciers behind them and cause faster melting and rise in sea levels than anticipated.
text_2: US and European scientists fear the collapse of ice shelves in Greenland and Antarctica will raise ocean levels faster than estimated, said a report published Friday in the journal Science.

text_1: An important source of vitamin D is sunshine which may explain people in warmer climates have more of it and a lower incidence of these cancers than people in more northern areas.
prev_text_1: There are no findings for darker skinned people.
text_2: Both studies found that taking 2000 international units of vitamin D3 daily, and a little sunshine could cut breast cancer cases by half and colorectal by two-thirds.
prev_text_2: Two new vitamin D studies, published by Moores Cancer Center, University of California, San Diego, in February 2007, revealed new prescriptions for preventing breast and colorectal cancers.

text_1: Johanna Dwyer of NIH cautioned that the public should not assume that vitamin D is a magic bullet and consume high amounts.
prev_text_1: One exception noted was that people with more vitamin D had a significantly lower risk of death from colorectal cancer.
text_2: The study cautioned that the issue is far from settled and advised people not to assume vitamin D is a cure-all and consume large doses.
prev_text_2: It found no sign that vitamin D lowered the overall risk of dying from cancer except for significantly lowering the risk of death from colorectal cancer.

tokens_2: In mid - November 2008 , pirates seized control of the Saudi - owned super oil tanker Sirius Star off the east coast of Africa for ransom and took it to Somalia .

text_1: Pirates out of southern mother ships seized the tanker in 16 minutes, using two speedboats.

tokens_1: China will invest billions to reverse desertification by building forests around cities and other areas and upgrading irrigation .
tokens_2: The government is investing $ 2.46 billion dollars in northwest China to reverse desertification by planting trees , upgrading irrigation facilities , and setting up monitoring stations .

text_1: China is investing billions of yuan to reverse desertification.
prev_text_1: China's breadbasket regions are in danger of losing fertility.
text_2: The government is investing $2.46 billion dollars in northwest China to reverse desertification by planting trees, upgrading irrigation facilities, and setting up monitoring stations.
prev_text_2: China, with an estimated 40 percent of its territory suffering from soil erosion, is taking conservation measures all over the country.

text_1: The Arctic's atmosphere is warming twice as fast as elsewhere on earth, and experts have warned that the region's ice could melt away completely by the end of this century, endangering many animal species and the traditional lifestyle of Inuits and Lapplanders.

tokens_2: At least six people were killed and 79 injured when steel arched 8 lane bridge collapsed over the Mississippi River plunging vehicles and massive chunks of concrete into the rushing waters .

text_2: The governor said the bridge had been inspected and had no major problems.
prev_text_2: The bridge was undergoing repairs at the time.

text_1: If current trends continue, Mead might never completely refill.
